    "# Downstream analysis on spatial multi-omics data of human gastric cancer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ebec567",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this tutorial, we will perform downstream analysis of spatial multi-omics data from the human gastric cancer, including identification of MCC flow, group-level MCC, MCC pattern, MCC remodelling in receiver cells."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "fe28695d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "import os\n",
    "import metachat as mc\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import scanpy as sc\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib import rcParams\n",
    "rcParams['pdf.fonttype'] = 42\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\", category=FutureWarning)"
   ]

    "## Import MetaChat results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "8ecbb603",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "adata = sc.read('datasets/human_gastric_cancer/metachat_result.h5ad')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ee597d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Compute group-level MCC of all pairs and all pathways"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "77d02cb1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To summarize MCC patterns between any two group types, we need to compute group-level MCCs across all metabolite–sensor pairs and all pathways."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "7cbbbd4a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# extract all_ms_pairs\n",
    "df_metasen_filtered = adata.uns['df_metasen_filtered']\n",
    "all_ms_pairs = (df_metasen_filtered['HMDB.ID'] + '-' + df_metasen_filtered['Sensor.Gene']).tolist()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "eebc1c29",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# extract all_metapathways\n",
    "Metapathway_data = df_metasen_filtered[\"Metabolite.Pathway\"].copy()\n",
    "Metapathway_list = []\n",
    "for item in Metapathway_data:\n",
    "    split_items = item.split('; ')\n",
    "    Metapathway_list.extend(split_items)\n",
    "all_metapathways = np.unique(Metapathway_list).tolist()\n",
    "all_metapathways = [x for x in all_metapathways if x != 'nan']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b6ef8516",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The original output of MetaChat provides MCC signals for each individual metabolite–sensor pair.\n",
    "Here, we use `mc.tl.summary_communication` to summarize the overall MCC activity associated with specific metabolic pathway, aggregating their communication strengths across all corresponding sensors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "ce350e7f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mc.tl.summary_communication(adata = adata,\n",
    "                            database_name = 'MetaChatDB',\n",
    "                            sum_metapathways = all_metapathways)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1ebf18d9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Meanwhile, all metabolite–sensor pairs and pathways can be processed together in parallel using the `use_parallel=True` option. Here, we use the non-spatial version of the statistical test for all metabolite–sensor pairs, since only the group-level MCC scores (rather than p-values) are needed in downstream analyses, allowing faster computation while retaining the same information content."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "2b012598",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "  Computing group-level MCC: 100%|██████████| 610/610 [00:19<00:00, 31.70it/s]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mc.tl.communication_group(adata = adata,\n",
    "                          database_name = 'MetaChatDB',\n",
    "                          group_name = \"tissue_type\",\n",
    "                          sum_ms_pairs = all_ms_pairs,\n",
    "                          n_permutations = 100,\n",
    "                          use_parallel = True,\n",
    "                          n_jobs = 100)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "a015da46",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mc.tl.communication_group_spatial(adata = adata,\n",
    "                                  database_name = 'MetaChatDB',\n",
    "                                  group_name = \"tissue_type\",\n",
    "                                  sum_metapathways = all_metapathways,\n",
    "                                  n_permutations = 100,\n",
    "                                  use_parallel = True,\n",
    "                                  n_jobs = 100)"
   ]
  },

    "We can observe significant interactions from the tumor tissue toward the surrounding gland regions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8ebd2fbc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary MCC pattern from tumor tissue to glands"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c90237e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this step, we summarize the MCC pattern specifically from the tumor tissue to the surrounding glands.\n",
    "By specifying the sender and receiver groups, the `mc.tl.summary_pathway` function integrates all metabolite–sensor pairs within each pathway and evaluates their overall contributions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "8d4e5e9b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sender_group = \"Tumor tissue\"\n",
    "receiver_group = \"Tumor and glands\"\n",
    "metapathway_rank, senspathway_rank, ms_result, metapathway_pair_contributions = mc.tl.summary_pathway(\n",
    "    adata = adata,\n",
    "    database_name = 'MetaChatDB',\n",
    "    group_name = \"tissue_type\",\n",
    "    sender_group = sender_group,\n",
    "    receiver_group = receiver_group,\n",
    "    permutation_spatial = True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a61dc2c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The function mc.tl.summary_pathway() outputs four complementary tables that summarize group-level MCC at multiple biological levels:  \n",
    "\n",
    "•\t`metapathway_rank` lists metabolite pathways ranked by their overall communication score, indicating which metabolic routes most contribute to the MCC between the selected sender and receiver groups.  \n",
    "\n",
    "•\t`senspathway_rank` ranks sensor-associated signaling pathways by their Rankscore, reflecting how strongly each receptor or signaling cascade is involved in receiving or responding to metabolite-mediated communication.  \n",
    "\n",
    "•\t`ms_result` is a matrix showing pairwise communication scores between each metabolite pathway and sensor pathway, capturing how specific metabolic routes couple to particular receptor signaling modules.  \n",
    "\n",
    "•\t`metapathway_pair_contributions` provides detailed contributions from individual metabolite–sensor pairs within each metabolite pathway, allowing fine-grained inspection of which molecular interactions drive the observed pathway-level MCC.  \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e8cc40b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sender_group = \"Tumor tissue\"\n",
    "receiver_group = \"Tumor and glands\"\n",
    "mc.pl.plot_summary_pathway(ms_result = ms_result,\n",
    "                           metapathway_rank = metapathway_rank,\n",
    "                           senspathway_rank = senspathway_rank,\n",
    "                           plot_metapathway_index = [2,3,5,7,8],\n",
    "                           plot_senspathway_index = [0,1,3,5,16],\n",
    "                           figsize = (8,4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "898e7e01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<img src=\"../../_static/image/plot_sanky.png\" alt=\"plot_sanky\" width=\"1000\"/>"

    "We can optionally remove ribosomal and mitochondrial genes from the analysis to reduce background noise and focus on biologically relevant communication response genes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "6ba15549",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import re\n",
    "pattern = re.compile(r'^(RPL|RPS|MT\\-|NDU|CO|ATP5)')\n",
    "mask = ~df_deg.index.to_series().str.match(pattern)\n",
    "df_deg = df_deg[mask].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "df_deg_clus, df_yhat_clus = mc.tl.communication_responseGenes_cluster(df_deg.iloc[:,:3], df_yhat, deg_clustering_res=0.3)"
